By applying different circuit loads, three different current densities (i.e., 2, 5 and 8 mA∙cm−2) were applied to control the yield and selectivity of this process (Fig. 3d, upper panel, and Fig. 3e). All the energy was from the electrochemical energy of our system, and did not cost extra energy. A piece of bipolar membrane was employed to separate the neutral pH condition of CO2RR and the alkaline Zn/Zn(II) redox pair. The electrochemical reactions on each side are described by the following equations:1Onnano - Auelectrode : CO2+2e-+2H+→CO + H2O\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
